        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q9259"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q7809/participant"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N16_VC_20_SCA/event/ev3"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Mountain_landscape_and_reference_chains"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N16_VC_20_SCA"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/60.9_7.166667"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The reference mountain chain of this VC is Scandinavean Mountains - Scandes. The reference mountain landscape of this VC is Aurland. The MRL covers the Aurland Fiord and the Nærøyfjorden, which are both branches of the world&amp;apos;s largest fiord, the Sognefjorden. The area is dominated by fiords and mountains. The Nærøyfjorden is part of The West Norwegian Fjords of Geirangefjord and Nærøyfjord UNESCO World Heritage Site. Most of the urban settlements are small villages in the shore of the fiords and on small river valleys. Aurland&amp;apos;s coat of arms depicts a goat, representing the importance of these animals and the cheese made out of their milk for the cultural identity of the MRL.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


